## Better Solution

### Intuition

* Repeatedly scanning the array is inefficient, so we store information about what we have already seen.
* Create an extra structure that directly represents all possible numbers.
* As we read the array, simply mark the numbers that appear.
* After marking everything, the unmarked position reveals the missing value.
* This works because every valid number gets its own dedicated place.
* It is faster than brute force since we avoid repeated searches.

### Approach

* Create an extra list to track which numbers appear.
* Mark each number found in the given list.
* Scan the full range and find the number that was never marked.
* Return that number as the missing value.

