### Pseudo Code


<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
missingNumber(arr, n) {
    /* 
       Create a temporary array temp of size n + 1. Initialize all values to 0.
       Index 0 is unused to simplify direct mapping of values 1..n.
    */
    temp[0..n] = 0
    /* Mark the numbers that are present in the input array. Traverse the array of size (n - 1). */
    for i = 0 to n - 2 {
        /* Use the value arr[i] as an index. Mark temp[arr[i]] = 1 to indicate presence. */
        temp[arr[i]] = 1
    }
    /* Scan numbers from 1 to n. The index with value 0 indicates the missing number. */
    for i = 1 to n {
        /* If temp[i] is still 0, i was never present */
        if temp[i] == 0 {
            return i
        }
    }
    /* Edge case: If no missing number is found, return -1 to indicate failure. */
    return -1
}
```

</CodeBlock>

