### Pseudo Code


<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
missingNumber(arr, n) {
    /* XOR has the property: a ^ a = 0 and a ^ 0 = a, which helps identify the missing number. */
    /* Initialize xor1 to store XOR of all array elements */
    xor1 = 0
    /* Initialize xor2 to store XOR of numbers from 1 to n-1 */
    xor2 = 0
    /* Traverse the array and compute XOR of array elements and 1..n-1 */
    for i = 0 to n - 2 {
        /* XOR current array element into xor1 */
        xor1 = xor1 ^ arr[i]
        /* XOR current number (i + 1) into xor2 */
        xor2 = xor2 ^ (i + 1)
    }
    /* The missing number is obtained by XORing xor1, xor2, and n. This cancels out all present numbers and leaves the missing number. */
    return xor1 ^ xor2 ^ n
}
```

</CodeBlock>

