# Check if an Array is Sorted

## Solution

### Intuition

* In an ascending array, every element should be less than or equal to the next one.
* So we only need to check neighboring pairs from left to right.
* If any pair breaks this rule (left > right), it is not sorted.
* If no such break is found, the array is sorted.

### Approach

- Iterate through the array.

- If at any point, an element is greater than its next element, return False.

- If the loop completes without finding such a pair, return True.

