### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
print_subseq(i, v, arr, n) {
    /* Recursive function to print all subsequences of the array arr */
    /* i: current index in the array */
    /* v: vector storing the current subsequence */
    /* arr: input array */
    /* n: size of the array */

    if i >= n {
        /* Base case: reached the end of the array */
        for each k in v {
            /* Print each element in the current subsequence */
            print k, " "
        }
        print newline /* Move to next line after printing one subsequence */
        return
    }

    /* Case 1: Do not include arr[i] in the current subsequence */
    print_subseq(i + 1, v, arr, n)

    /* Case 2: Include arr[i] in the current subsequence */
    v.push_back(arr[i]) /* Add current element to the subsequence */
    print_subseq(i + 1, v, arr, n) /* Recurse for next index */
    v.pop_back() /* Backtrack: remove the last element to explore other subsequences */
}

```

</CodeBlock>

