# Remove Specific Element

## Solution

### Intuition

* We only need to keep the values that are different from the given target and place them at the front of the array.
* As we scan the array, every valid value can be copied to the next free spot at the beginning.
* This works because the relative order of kept elements stays the same, and we do not need any extra array.

### Approach

* Start from the beginning of the array and track the next position where a kept value should go.
* Scan every element of the array once.
* Whenever the current value is not equal to the target, place it at the next free position in the front part of the array.
* After the scan finishes, return how many values were kept.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
removeSpecificElement(arr, target) {

    /* Store the next position where a non-target element should be placed */
    pos = 0

    /* Scan the entire array once to keep only valid elements */
    for i = 0 to arr.size() - 1 {

        /* Only keep the current element if it is different from the target */
        if arr[i] != target {

            /* Move the current valid element to the next free position in front */
            arr[pos] = arr[i]

            /* Advance the position for the next valid element */
            pos = pos + 1
        }
    }

    /* Return the number of elements that remain after removal */
    return pos
}
```

</CodeBlock>

