# Quick Sort

### Intuition

Quick sort is based on the idea of pick a *pivot* and place it in the right spot.

* Choose one element as a *pivot*.
* Rearrange the array so that:

  * all elements smaller than the *pivot* go to the left,
  * all elements greater than the *pivot* go to the right.
* After this “partition” step, the pivot is already in its final sorted position.

Now the problem becomes smaller:

* Sort the left part (elements < pivot)
* Sort the right part (elements > pivot)

This repeats recursively, so the array gets sorted by continuously splitting into smaller subarrays around pivots.

*Main idea:* partition around a pivot, then sort the two halves.

### Approach

* Choose a *pivot* element from the array (commonly the first, last, middle, or a random element).
* Partition the array around the *pivot*:

   * Move all elements smaller than pivot to the left side.
   * Move all elements greater than pivot to the right side.
   * After partitioning, the pivot ends up in its correct sorted position.
* Recursively apply quick sort on the left subarray (elements before pivot).
* Recursively apply quick sort on the right subarray (elements after pivot).
* Stop recursion when a subarray has size `0` or `1` (already sorted).

### Dry Run

<div style="position: relative; width: 100%; padding-bottom: 59.27%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;">
  <iframe 
    src="https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vSyYMTuFk7mmj2mGD9-yMVmV18J-z7fK8XPxFxEvtMV3DAacmAjYMU0WQT9nNAbUwpYSPZbRSPXhKHq/pubembed?start=false&loop=false&delayms=3000" 
    style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border: 0;" 
    allowfullscreen="true" 
    mozallowfullscreen="true" 
    webkitallowfullscreen="true">
  </iframe>
</div>

### Pseudo Code


<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```Pseudo
partitionArr(arr, low, high) {
    /*
    Choose the first element as pivot
    Place pivot in its correct sorted position
    Return the pivot index after partitioning
    */

    i = low
    j = high

    pivot = arr[low]

    /* Move i and j towards each other and swap misplaced elements */
    while (i < j) {

        /* Move i right until an element > pivot is found (stay inside bounds) */
        while (i <= high - 1 && arr[i] <= pivot) {
            i = i + 1
        }

        /* Move j left until an element <= pivot is found (stay inside bounds) */
        while (j >= low + 1 && arr[j] > pivot) {
            j = j - 1
        }

        /* Swap if pointers have not crossed */
        if (i < j) {
            swap(arr[i], arr[j])
        }
    }

    /* Put pivot in its correct position (index j) */
    swap(arr[low], arr[j])

    return j
}

quickSortRec(arr, low, high) {
    /*
    Recursively sort the array using partitioning
    */

    if (low < high) {
        /* Partition and get pivot's final index */
        pivot_index = partitionArr(arr, low, high)

        /* Sort left side of pivot */
        quickSortRec(arr, low, pivot_index - 1)

        /* Sort right side of pivot */
        quickSortRec(arr, pivot_index + 1, high)
    }
}

quickSort(arr, n) {
    /*
    Driver function for quick sort
    */

    if (n <= 1) {
        return
    }

    quickSortRec(arr, 0, n - 1)
}

```
</CodeBlock>

### Code Implementation

<MultiLanguageCodeBlock enableMoveCode={true}>

```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class solution {
    int partitionArr(int arr[], int low, int high) {
        int i = low;
        int j = high;

        int pivot = arr[low];

        while (i < j) {
            while (i <= high - 1 && arr[i] <= pivot) {
                i++;
            }

            while (j >= low + 1 && arr[j] > pivot) {
                j--;
            }

            if (i < j) {
                swap(arr[i], arr[j]);
            }
        }

        swap(arr[low], arr[j]);
        return j;
    }

    void quickSortRec(int arr[], int low, int high) {
        if (low < high) {
            int pivot_index = partitionArr(arr, low, high);
            quickSortRec(arr, low, pivot_index - 1);
            quickSortRec(arr, pivot_index + 1, high);
        }
    }

public:
    void quickSort(int arr[], int n) {
        if (n <= 1) return;
        quickSortRec(arr, 0, n - 1);
    }
};

