### Complexity Analysis

**Time Complexity:**

* **Best case:** **O(n log n)**

  * Happens when the *pivot* splits the array into two nearly equal halves each time.

* **Average case:** **O(n log n)**

  * On typical/random inputs, partitioning is reasonably balanced.

* **Worst case:** **O(n²)**

  * Happens when the *pivot* is always the smallest or largest element (since *pivot* is `arr[low]`), e.g.:

    * already sorted array (ascending)
    * reverse sorted array (descending)
    * many equal elements (can also lead to poor splits)

Each partition takes **O(n)**, and in the worst case the recursion becomes `n + (n-1) + ... + 1`.

<br>
