# Most Frequent Element 

## Frequency Counting with Hash Map

### Intuition

* We need the value that appears the most times, so the first natural idea is to count how often each value occurs.
* Once we know every count, we can keep track of the largest one and the value attached to it.
* This works because the value with the highest count is exactly the answer, and it avoids checking the same value again and again.

### Approach

* Create a frequency table to store how many times each value appears.
* Go through the array once and update the count for each value.
* While counting, keep track of the highest frequency seen so far.
* Whenever a value gets a higher count than the current best, store it as the answer.
* Return the stored value after finishing the scan.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
mostFrequentElement(nums, n) {

    /* If the array is empty, there is no frequent element to return */
    if n == 0 {

        /* Return a failure value for the empty case */
        return -1
    }

    /* Store how many times each value appears */
    freq = empty map

    /* Keep track of the best answer seen so far */
    answer = nums[0]

    /* Keep track of the highest frequency seen so far */
    maxFreq = 0

    /* Traverse the array and update frequencies */
    for i = 0 to n - 1 {

        /* Increase the count of the current value */
        freq[nums[i]] = freq[nums[i]] + 1

        /* Check whether the current value became the most frequent */
        if freq[nums[i]] > maxFreq {

            /* Update the best frequency because a better answer was found */
            maxFreq = freq[nums[i]]

            /* Store the current value as the most frequent element */
            answer = nums[i]
        }
    }

    /* Return the element with the highest recorded frequency */
    return answer
}
```

</CodeBlock>

### Code Implementation

<MultiLanguageCodeBlock enableMoveCode={true}>

```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class solution {
public:
    int mostFrequentElement(int n, vector<int>& nums) {
        unordered_map<int, int> freq;
        int answer = nums[0];
        int maxFreq = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            freq[nums[i]]++;

            if (freq[nums[i]] > maxFreq) {
                maxFreq = freq[nums[i]];
                answer = nums[i];
            }
        }

        return answer;
    }
};

