### Complexity Analysis

* **Time Complexity: `O(n^2)`**

  * Each call to `computeMin()` scans the full array once and then processes the built frequency map, so one call takes `O(n)`.
  * `minimumBalls()` evaluates the full array case once and then tries excluding each of the `n` indices, giving `n + 1` total calls.
  * The dominant term is `O(n^2)` because we recompute the grouped total from scratch for every possible exclusion.

* **Space Complexity: `O(n)`**

  * The map `mp` stores the frequencies of distinct reported values for one scenario, which can take up to `O(n)` space.
  * Only constant extra variables are used outside the map.
  * Total space used is `O(n)`.

## Solution 2: Optimal Solution

### Intuition

* Recomputing the whole answer after removing each ball repeats a lot of work.
* The total contribution of one reported value depends only on how many times that value appears.
* So we can first compute the answer for the full array once.
* When one report is ignored, only the frequency of that one reported value changes, so only that group needs to be recalculated.
* This lets us test every possible ignored report in constant time after preprocessing.

### Approach

* Count how many times each reported value appears in the array.
* For every distinct value, compute its full contribution to the answer and add it to a baseline total.
* Also store each value’s contribution separately.
* For every index, pretend that report is ignored by reducing the frequency of its value by one.
* Recompute only that value’s contribution, replace the old contribution in the baseline, and update the minimum answer.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
minimumBalls(counts) {

    /* Store how many times each reported value appears */
    map freq

    /* Count the frequency of every report */
    for num of counts {
        freq[num]++
    }

    /* Initialize the baseline answer using all reports */
    ans = 0

    /* Store each reported value's current contribution to the total */
    map grpTotal

    /* Build the baseline total from every distinct reported value */
    for it : freq {

        /* Convert the report into the actual group size */
        curr = it.first + 1

        /* Get how many balls reported this value */
        cnt = it.second

        /* Round up to the minimum full groups needed for this value */
        res = ceil((double)cnt / curr) * curr

        /* Save this contribution so it can be replaced later */
        grpTotal[curr - 1] = res

        /* Add the contribution to the baseline total */
        ans += res
    }

    /* Preserve the full-array answer before testing exclusions */
    minBalls = ans

    /* Try ignoring each report and update only its affected group */
    for i = 0 to counts.size() - 1 {

        /* Get the actual group size for this report */
        curr = counts[i] + 1

        /* Reduce the frequency of this reported value by one */
        cnt = freq[curr - 1] - 1

        /* Recompute the contribution after excluding this report */
        res = ceil((double)cnt / curr) * curr

        /* Retrieve the original contribution of this value */
        val = grpTotal[curr - 1]

        /* Replace only this group's contribution and keep the minimum */
        ans = min(ans, minBalls - val + res)
    }

    /* Return the smallest valid total found */
    return ans
}
```

</CodeBlock>

### Code Implementation

<MultiLanguageCodeBlock enableMoveCode={true}>

```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class solution {
public:
    int minimumBalls(vector<int>& counts) {
        int n = counts.size();
        unordered_map<int, int> freq;

        for (int num : counts) {
            freq[num]++;
        }

        int ans = 0;
        unordered_map<int, int> grpTotal;

        for (auto& it : freq) {
            int curr = it.first + 1;
            int cnt = it.second;
            int res = ceil((double)cnt / curr) * curr;
            grpTotal[curr - 1] = res;
            ans += res;
        }

        int minBalls = ans;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int curr = counts[i] + 1;
            int cnt = freq[curr - 1] - 1;
            int res = ceil((double)cnt / curr) * curr;
            int val = grpTotal[curr - 1];
            ans = min(ans, minBalls - val + res);
        }

        return ans;
    }
};

