### Complexity Analysis

* **Time Complexity: `O(n)`**

  * Insertion into the queue takes constant time for each element.
  * A frequency query scans all elements of the queue once using a temporary copy.
  * The dominant term is `O(n)` because each query may require checking the entire queue.

* **Space Complexity: `O(n)`**

  * A temporary copy of the queue is created while answering a frequency query.
  * Aside from that copy, only a few extra variables are used.
  * Total space used is `O(n)`.

# Special Stack Operations

## Solution

### Intuition

* A normal stack can easily handle pushing and popping, but finding the minimum every time becomes slow if we scan the whole stack again and again.
* The key idea is to keep one more stack that stores the smallest value seen so far at every step.
* Then the top of the extra stack always gives the current minimum in constant time, while every push and pop stays fast too.

### Approach

* Keep one stack for the actual values and another stack for the minimum value at each position.
* For every push, add the value to the main stack and also add the new minimum to the second stack.
* For every pop, remove the top element from both stacks and return the removed value from the main stack.
* For checking emptiness, see whether the main stack has any element left.
* For minimum queries, return the top value of the second stack, or return failure when the stack is empty.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
specialStack(queries) {

    /* Create one stack for actual values and one stack for tracking the minimum at every level */
    st = empty stack
    minSt = empty stack

    /* Store answers for operations that produce output */
    ans = empty list

    /* Process each command in the given order */
    for each query in queries {

        /* Break the current command into words so we can identify the operation */
        parts = split query by space

        /* Handle insertion into the stack */
        if parts[0] == "push" {

            /* Read the value that must be inserted */
            x = integer value of parts[1]

            /* Insert the value into the main stack */
            push x into st

            /* If this is the first element, it is also the minimum */
            if minSt is empty {

                /* Store the first minimum */
                push x into minSt
            }
            else {

                /* Compare with the current minimum and store the smaller one */
                currMin = top of minSt
                newMin = minimum of x and currMin

                /* Save the minimum for this stack level */
                push newMin into minSt
            }
        }

        /* Handle removal from the stack */
        else if parts[0] == "pop" {

            /* If the stack is empty, return failure for this command */
            if st is empty {

                /* Record failure because nothing can be removed */
                add "-1" to ans
            }
            else {

                /* Save the removed value before deleting it */
                topVal = top of st

                /* Remove one level from both stacks to keep them aligned */
                pop from st
                pop from minSt

                /* Record the removed value */
                add string form of topVal to ans
            }
        }

        /* Handle the empty check */
        else if parts[0] == "isEmpty" {

            /* Return true when no element exists, otherwise false */
            if st is empty {

                /* Record the result for this command */
                add "true" to ans
            }
            else {

                /* Record the result for this command */
                add "false" to ans
            }
        }

        /* Handle the minimum query */
        else if parts[0] == "getMin" {

            /* If no element exists, minimum cannot be reported */
            if minSt is empty {

                /* Record failure because the stack is empty */
                add "-1" to ans
            }
            else {

                /* The top of the minimum stack is the current minimum */
                add string form of top of minSt to ans
            }
        }
    }

    /* Return all outputs in the same order as the output-producing commands */
    return ans
}
```

