## Solution 2: Built-in GCD Function

### Intuition

* Many languages already provide a ready-made way to compute the greatest common divisor.

* This is useful when we want the same result without writing the full logic ourselves.

* It is simple and clean, while still giving the same efficient performance.

### Approach

* Read the two input numbers.

* Use the language’s available greatest common divisor utility to compute the answer.

* Return that result directly.

* Add a fallback return for invalid cases.

### Pseudocode

```customtext
gcd(a, b) {
    /* Handle valid positive input using the built-in utility */
    if a > 0 && b > 0 {
        gcdValue = gcd(a, b)
        return gcdValue
    }

    /* Fallback return for invalid input */
    return -1
}
```

