# BS - Find Nth root of M (N√M)

## Using Linear Search

### Intuition

Finding the Nth root of a number means discovering a value which, when multiplied by itself N times, equals the target.

Start with the simplest idea: try all possible candidates one by one. For each candidate, calculate its Nth power and compare with the target.

If the power matches, that’s the root. If it becomes larger than the target, further numbers will only grow bigger, so you can stop early.

This brute-force thought naturally leads to checking each number linearly until the correct root is found or proven absent.

### Approach

* Multiply a number by itself repeatedly to get its power.
* Check each number from 1 up to the target to see if its power equals the given value.
* Return the number if it matches, otherwise indicate no integer root exists.
* Stop early if the power exceeds the target.

### Dry Run

