# Vector Operations Challenge

## Dynamic Array Simulation

### Intuition

* The operations must happen in the same order as the input, so the most natural idea is to directly simulate them on a dynamic array.
* Insertion at the end, reversing the whole array, printing the array, and checking its size all match standard dynamic array behavior.
* Deleting a value needs a linear search to find its first occurrence, so this method is simple and correct, but some operations can take linear time.

### Approach

* Keep one dynamic array to store the current elements.
* Read each operation and update the array based on the command.
* For insertion, add the given value at the end of the array.
* For deletion, find the first matching value and remove it if it exists.
* For reversing, flip the current order of the array, and for size or print, output the requested result.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
processOperations(operations) {

    /* Store all current elements in a dynamic array so every command updates the same state */
    arr = empty list

    /* Process each command one by one in the given order */
    for each operation in operations {

        /* Split the command so we can identify its type and optional value */
        parts = split operation by spaces

        /* If the command asks to insert, append the given value at the end */
        if parts[0] == "insert" {

            /* Read the value that must be added to the array */
            x = convert parts[1] to integer

            /* Add the new value at the end to preserve insertion order */
            append x to arr
        }

        /* If the command asks to delete, remove only the first matching value */
        else if parts[0] == "delete" {

            /* Read the value that must be removed if present */
            x = convert parts[1] to integer

            /* Search the array from left to right to find the first occurrence */
            for i = 0 to size of arr - 1 {

                /* Remove the first matching value and stop so only one occurrence is deleted */
                if arr[i] == x {
                    erase arr[i]
                    break
                }
            }
        }

        /* If the command asks to reverse, flip the current order of all elements */
        else if parts[0] == "reverse" {

            /* Reverse the whole array in place */
            reverse arr
        }

        /* If the command asks for the size, output the current number of elements */
        else if parts[0] == "size" {

            /* Print the number of stored elements */
            output size of arr
        }

        /* If the command asks to print, show all elements in their current order */
        else if parts[0] == "print" {

            /* Print an empty line when the array has no elements */
            if size of arr == 0 {
                output empty line
            }

            /* Otherwise print all elements separated by spaces */
            else {
                output all elements of arr separated by spaces
            }
        }
    }

    /* All commands have been processed */
    return
}
```

