# Longest Subarray with Sum K

## Solution 1: Brute Force Solution

### Intuition

* The most direct idea is to generate every possible subarray and check its sum.
* For each chosen start and end position, we can scan that segment and calculate its total from scratch.
* This always gives the correct answer because no subarray is skipped, but it is very slow due to repeated work.

### Approach

* Pick every possible starting position in the array.
* For each starting position, pick every possible ending position.
* For each chosen segment, calculate its total by scanning all elements inside it.
* If the total matches the target, update the maximum length found so far.
* Return the longest valid length at the end.

### Pseudocode

```customtext
longestSubarrayWithSumK(arr, n, k) {
    /* Store the best length found so far */
    maxLen = 0

    /* Try every possible starting index */
    for i = 0 to n - 1 {

        /* Try every possible ending index */
        for j = i to n - 1 {

            /* Compute the sum of the current subarray from scratch */
            sum = 0
            for x = i to j {
                sum = sum + arr[x]
            }

            /* Check whether the current subarray matches the target */
            if sum == k {

                /* Compute the current subarray length */
                len = j - i + 1

                /* Update the best answer if this subarray is longer */
                if len > maxLen {
                    maxLen = len
                }
            }
        }
    }

    /* Return the longest valid length or 0 if none exists */
    return maxLen
}
```

### Code Implementation

<MultiLanguageCodeBlock enableMoveCode={true}>

```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class solution {
public:
    int longestSubarrayWithSumK(int arr[], int n, long long k) {
        int maxLen = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = i; j < n; j++) {
                long long sum = 0;

                for (int x = i; x <= j; x++) {
                    sum += arr[x];
                }

                if (sum == k) {
                    int len = j - i + 1;
                    maxLen = max(maxLen, len);
                }
            }
        }

        return maxLen;
    }
};

