# Find Stable Position in Array

## Solution 1: Recompute Left and Right Sums for Every Index

### Intuition

* For each position, we directly check whether the array is balanced there.
* We compute the sum of all elements on the left side and the sum of all elements on the right side.
* If both sums match, that index is the first stable position.
* This method is straightforward, but it repeats a lot of work because sums are recalculated again and again.

### Approach

* Traverse every index of the array one by one.
* For each index, compute the left-side sum by scanning all elements before it.
* Compute the right-side sum by scanning all elements after it.
* As soon as both sums become equal, return that index.
* If no index satisfies the condition, return -1.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
findStablePosition(arr) {
    /* Store the size of the array */
    n = size of arr

    /* Check every index as a possible stable position */
    for (i from 0 to n - 1) {
        /* Store sum of elements on the left side */
        leftSum = 0
        /* Store sum of elements on the right side */
        rightSum = 0

        /* Compute sum of all elements before index i */
        for (j from 0 to i - 1) {
            leftSum = leftSum + arr[j]
        }

        /* Compute sum of all elements after index i */
        for (j from i + 1 to n - 1) {
            rightSum = rightSum + arr[j]
        }

        /* Return i if both sums are equal */
        if (leftSum equals rightSum) {
            return i
        }
    }

    /* No stable position exists */
    return -1
}
```

</CodeBlock>

