# Remove the Rightmost Set Bit

### Intuition 

* Look at the binary form of the number.

* Notice that the rightmost `1` is the first position that makes the number “different” from the previous number when decreased by `1`.

* By combining the original number with the number just before it, you can turn that rightmost `1` into `0` while keeping all other bits the same.

* This gives a simple way to remove the last `1` without touching the rest of the number.

### Approach 

* Look at the binary form of the number and identify the last `1` from the right.

* Subtracting `1` flips bits up to the rightmost `1`, which can be combined with the original number.

* Use this to remove the rightmost 1 while keeping other bits unchanged.


### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">
```pseudocode
removeRightmostSetBit(n) {

    return n AND (n - 1)
}
```
