##Solution 2 : Optimal (Using Bitwise operation)

###Intuition 

* A number that is a power of `2` has only *one bit set* in its representation.

* Subtracting `1` from it flips that bit and all lower bits.

* If there was only one bit set, combining the number and the result of subtracting 1 will *eliminate all bits*, leaving nothing.

* So, checking for this “elimination” tells us if the number had only one set bit → it’s a power of `2`.

### Approach

* Check if the number is positive since only positive numbers can be powers of two.

* Use a simple trick to see if there is exactly one set bit in the number.

* If there is only one set bit, the number is a power of two; otherwise, it is not.

