# Sum of Squares of 1 to N

## Recursive Solution

### Intuition

* The sum from 1 to n can be built step by step.
* For any value n, the answer is the square of n plus the answer for n - 1.
* This naturally fits recursion because the same smaller problem keeps repeating.
* Once we reach 1, the recursion stops.

### Approach

* Start with the base case where n is 1 and return 1.
* For any other value, add the square of the current number to the result for n - 1.
* Keep reducing n until the base case is reached.
* Return the accumulated sum as the recursion unwinds.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
recursiveSumOfSquares(n) {
    /* Base case: when n is 1, return its square */
    if (n == 1) {
        return 1
    }

    /* Recursive case: add square of current number to answer for n - 1 */
    return n * n + recursiveSumOfSquares(n - 1)
}
```

</CodeBlock>

### Code Implementation

