# Multiplication Table Generator

## Iterative Multiplication from 1 to 10

### Intuition

* We need to print the same number multiplied by every value from `1` to `10`.
* The most natural idea is to go through these multipliers one by one and compute the product each time.
* This works because every required line follows the same pattern, so a simple loop can generate all of them in order.

### Approach

* Read the given number.
* Go through all values from `1` to `10`.
* For each value, multiply it with the given number.
* Print the result in the required multiplication format.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
table(n) {
    /* Iterate through all multipliers from 1 to 10 to generate the table */
    for i = 1 to 10 {

        /* Compute the product for the current multiplier */
        result = n * i

        /* Print the current multiplication statement in the required format */
        print n, " x ", i, " = ", result
    }

    /* Return a sentinel value because the work is complete */
    return
}
```

</CodeBlock>

### Code Implementation

