# Middle Element Multiplier

### Intuition 

* First, determine whether the size of the array is even or odd.

* If the size is odd, there is one clear middle element.

* If the size is even, there are two middle elements, so choose the first one.

* Multiply the selected middle element by the given value.

* Finally, print all the elements of the array to show the updated result.


### Approach

- Identify the middle element of the array.

  - If the array size is odd, pick the exact middle element.

  - If the array size is even, pick the first middle element.

- Multiply the identified middle element by `k`.

- Print all elements of the array in a space-separated format.

### Dry Run

