# Valid Anagram

## Solution 1 (Brute force Approach)

### Intuition

* Two strings can be anagrams only if they have the **same number of characters**, so the first quick check is whether their lengths match.
* An anagram is just a **rearrangement**, meaning both strings should contain the **same letters**. A simple way to make this easy to verify is to **arrange the letters of each string in the same order**.
* If we sort both strings, then any two anagrams will become **exactly identical after sorting**. So we sort and then compare; equal means anagram, otherwise not.

### Approach

- Check if the strings have the same length; if not, they can't be anagrams.

- Sort the characters in both strings.

- Compare the sorted strings; if they match, return true; otherwise, return false.

### Dry Run

