# Find Position in 2D Array

## Solution

### Intuition

* The matrix is not given in any sorted order, so the safest idea is to check every cell one by one.
* If we scan row by row, the moment we find the target, we also know its exact row and column position.
* This method is simple and always correct, but in the worst case it may need to inspect the entire matrix.

### Approach

* Traverse the matrix row by row.
* For each row, check every element from the first column to the last column.
* If the target is found, print its row index and column index, then stop immediately.
* If the full matrix is scanned and the target never appears, print `-1 -1`.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
/* Scan the matrix row by row to find the target value */
searchElement(arr, n, m, k) {

    /* Visit each row of the matrix */
    for i = 0 to n - 1 {

        /* Visit each column inside the current row */
        for j = 0 to m - 1 {

            /* Check whether the current cell contains the target */
            if arr[i][j] == k {

                /* Print the matching row and column indices */
                print(i, j)

                /* Stop immediately after finding the first match */
                return
            }
        }
    }

    /* The target does not exist anywhere in the matrix */
    print(-1, -1)

    /* End the function after reporting failure */
    return
}
```

</CodeBlock>

