  * Total space used is `O(1)`.

# Three Sum

## Solution 1: Brute Force Solution

### Intuition

* The most direct way is to try every possible combination of three different indices.
* For each triplet, check whether the sum is `0`.
* Since the same values can appear in different positions, duplicate triplets may be generated.
* To avoid duplicates, sort each valid triplet and store it in a set.

### Approach

* Use three nested loops to generate all possible triplets `(i, j, k)` such that `i < j < k`.
* If `arr[i] + arr[j] + arr[k] == 0`, create a temporary triplet.
* Sort that triplet so that the same combination always has the same form.
* Insert it into a set to keep only unique triplets.
* At the end, copy all triplets from the set into the answer list.

### Pseudocode

```customtext
threeSum(arr) {
    /* Store the size of the array */
    n = arr.size()

    /* Store unique triplets */
    s = empty set

    /* Try every possible triplet */
    for i = 0 to n - 1 {
        for j = i + 1 to n - 1 {
            for k = j + 1 to n - 1 {

                /* Check whether the current triplet sums to zero */
                if arr[i] + arr[j] + arr[k] == 0 {
                    temp = [arr[i], arr[j], arr[k]]
                    sort(temp)
                    insert temp into s
                }
            }
        }
    }

    /* Convert the set into the final answer list */
    ans = empty list
    for each triplet in s {
        add triplet to ans
    }

    return ans
}
```

### Code Implementation

<MultiLanguageCodeBlock enableMoveCode={true}>

```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> threeSum(vector<int>& arr) {
        int n = arr.size();
        set<vector<int>> s;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                for (int k = j + 1; k < n; k++) {
                    if (arr[i] + arr[j] + arr[k] == 0) {
                        vector<int> temp = {arr[i], arr[j], arr[k]};
                        sort(temp.begin(), temp.end());
                        s.insert(temp);
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        vector<vector<int>> ans;
        for (auto &triplet : s) {
            ans.push_back(triplet);
        }

        return ans;
    }
};

