## Backtracking Solution

### Intuition

* To print numbers in **descending order**, think of postponing the printing instead of printing immediately.

* Start from the smallest value and keep moving forward until reaching the limit.

* Do not print anything while moving forward — just continue the recursion.

* Once the recursion reaches the end, begin printing while returning.

* Because the last value reached is the largest, printing during the return phase naturally produces a **reverse (descending) sequence**.

### Approach

* Use recursion to first reach the largest number.
* Delay printing until the recursive calls finish.
* Print values while returning from recursion.
* This results in numbers printed in descending order.

