# Print Digits of a Number in Reverse Order

## Digit Extraction with Modulo and Division

### Intuition

* Since the digits are already needed from right to left, the last digit is the first thing we should take out.
* We can repeatedly remove the last digit and print it, so the digits naturally come out in reverse order.
* This works because each step reveals the current last digit and shortens the number for the next step.

### Approach

* Keep repeating until the number becomes zero.
* Take the last digit of the number.
* Print that digit on a new line.
* Remove the last digit from the number and continue.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
printDigit(N) {
    /* Keep processing until all digits have been printed */
    while N > 0 {

        /* Extract the current last digit because it is the next digit in reverse order */
        digit = N % 10

        /* Print the extracted digit on a new line */
        print digit

        /* Remove the last digit so the next iteration can process the remaining number */
        N = N / 10
    }

    /* All digits have been processed — return from the function */
    return
}
```

</CodeBlock>

