# Printing Divisors of an Integer in Ascending Order

## Solution

### Intuition

Divisors come in pairs. If `i` divides `n`, then `n/i` also divides `n`.

* Instead of checking all numbers from `1` to `n`, we only check up to √n.

* This ensures we catch both small and large divisors efficiently.

* Finally, sorting the collected divisors gives them in ascending order.

### Approach

* Check all possible divisors only up to the square root of the number.

* Whenever a divisor is found, include both the divisor and its pair.

* Store all divisors while scanning.

* Finally, sort them in increasing order before returning.

### Dry Run

<div style="position: relative; width: 100%; padding-bottom: 59.27%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;">
  <iframe 
    src="https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vR-EOlRJOYQO0sTg6g7OZWb1Zhk2UE0GVBRjarP-OHzXgummMJGgApFBDh7lPdqwmfNCGRz_JBFTPcv/pubembed?start=false&loop=false&delayms=3000" 
    style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border: 0;" 
    allowfullscreen="true" 
    mozallowfullscreen="true" 
    webkitallowfullscreen="true">
  </iframe>
</div>

### Pseudo Code


<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```pseudocode
printDivisors(n) {
    /* Create a list to store all divisors of n */
    divisors = empty list

    /* Iterate from 1 to square root of n */
    for i = 1 to while i * i <= n {
        /* If i divides n, it is a divisor */
        if n mod i == 0 {
            /* Add the divisor i */
            add i to divisors

            /* If i and n/i are different, add the paired divisor */
            if i != n / i {
                add (n / i) to divisors
            }
        }
    }

    /* Sort the divisors in ascending order */
    sort divisors

    /* Return the list of divisors */
    return divisors
}
```
</CodeBlock>

### Code Implementation

<MultiLanguageCodeBlock enableMoveCode={true}>

```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class solution {
public:
    vector<int> printDivisors(int n) {
        vector<int> divisors;

        for (int i = 1; i * i <= n; i++) {
            if (n % i == 0) {
                divisors.push_back(i);

                if (i != n / i) {
                    divisors.push_back(n / i);
                }
            }
        }

        sort(divisors.begin(), divisors.end());
        return divisors;
    }
};

