### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```
secondLargestDigit(num) {
    /* Create a frequency array to count how many times each digit appears */
    freq = array of size 10 filled with 0

    /* Copy num into temp so the original number remains unchanged */
    temp = num

    /* Extract each digit from temp and update its frequency */
    while temp > 0 {
        rem = temp % 10
        temp = temp / 10
        freq[rem]++
    }

    /* Initialize variables to track the largest and second largest digits */
    largest = -1
    secondlargest = -1

    /* Traverse digits from 9 down to 0 to find the second largest distinct digit */
    for i = 9 to 0 {
        /* Check if digit i exists in the number */
        if freq[i] > 0 {
            /* If the largest digit is already found, then current digit is the second largest */
            if largest != -1 {
                return i
            }
            else {
                /* Store the first found digit as the largest digit */
                largest = i
            }
        }
    }
    /* If there is no second largest distinct digit, return -1 */
    return -1
}
```

</CodeBlock>

