## Solution 2 (Single Pass)

### Intuition

* We need the **second largest distinct digit**, so while scanning the number, it is enough to remember only the **best two digits seen so far**.
* Whenever a new digit is larger than the current largest, the old largest naturally becomes the second largest.
* Otherwise, if the digit is smaller than the largest but still bigger than the current second largest, it should take the second spot.
* This way, the answer is built in **one traversal**, without extra storage or sorting.

### Approach 

* Go through each digit of the number one by one.
* Keep track of the biggest digit and the second biggest different digit seen so far.
* If a bigger digit is found, update both values properly; otherwise, update only the second biggest when needed.
* At the end, return the second largest distinct digit.

