# Sum of Digits Until Single Digit

## Brute Force Solution

### Intuition

* Keep summing the digits of the number until it becomes a single-digit number.

* Each iteration reduces the number’s magnitude because the sum of digits is smaller than the original number.

* Eventually, the number will be in the range `0–9`, which is the final result.

Why it works:

* Adding digits repeatedly is equivalent to repeatedly taking the sum modulo `9` (except when the number is a multiple of `9`).

* This process always converges to a single-digit number in `O(log n)` steps (number of digits in `num`).

### Approach

* Keep adding all digits of the number.

* If the sum has more than one digit, repeat the process on the sum.

* Continue until a single-digit number is obtained.

* Return this single-digit sum as the result.

### Dry Run

