# GCD of Array

## Iterative Euclidean GCD

### Intuition

* We need the greatest number that divides every element of the array.
* A useful observation is that the GCD of the whole array can be built step by step by taking the GCD of the current answer with the next element.
* This works because GCD is associative, so combining numbers one by one gives the same final result.

### Approach

* Start with the first element as the current answer.
* Traverse the remaining elements one by one.
* Update the current answer by finding the GCD of it and the current element.
* After processing all elements, return the final answer.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
gcd(N, arr) {

    /* Start with the first element because the final answer must divide it as well */
    ans = arr[0]

    /* Process every remaining element to gradually build the GCD of the whole array */
    for i = 1 to N - 1 {

        /* Replace the current answer with the GCD of the answer so far and the next element */
        ans = findGCD(ans, arr[i])
    }

    /* After all elements are processed, the current answer is the GCD of the entire array */
    return ans
}

findGCD(a, b) {

    /* Keep reducing the problem until the second value becomes zero */
    while b != 0 {

        /* Store the remainder because it becomes the next smaller subproblem */
        rem = a % b

        /* Shift the second value into the first position for the next step */
        a = b

        /* Continue with the remainder as the new second value */
        b = rem
    }

    /* When the second value becomes zero, the first value is the GCD */
    return a
}
```

</CodeBlock>

### Code Implementation

<MultiLanguageCodeBlock enableMoveCode={true}>

```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class solution {
public:
    int findGCD(int a, int b) {
        while (b != 0) {
            int rem = a % b;
            a = b;
            b = rem;
        }
        return a;
    }

    int gcd(int N, int arr[]) {
        int ans = arr[0];
        for (int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
            ans = findGCD(ans, arr[i]);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

