# Reverse of an Array

## Iteration Approach 1

### Intuition

* Use **two positions**, one from the start and one from the end.

* Swap the elements at these positions.

* Move both positions **towards the center**.

* When they meet, the array is fully reversed.

### Approach

* Start with one position at the beginning and one at the end.
* Swap the elements from both sides.
* Keep moving inward until both positions meet.

### Dry Run

<div style="position: relative; width: 100%; padding-bottom: 59.27%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;">
  <iframe 
    src="https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vT_i5QtncP2m6hcDD6IOV5vC2_LlZgI205yCD6qTd8_ppRdQEyWCHvXfuEBRXKoEqmpKvhr26w7Kf_C/pubembed?start=false&loop=false&delayms=3000" 
