## Iteration Approach 2

### Intuition

* To reverse an array, only the **first half needs processing**.

* Each element in the first half is swapped with its matching element from the end.

* After all swaps, the array becomes reversed.

* No extra memory is needed since changes happen **in place**.

### Approach

* Traverse only half of the elements from the beginning.
* Swap each element with the corresponding element from the end.
* This reverses the array without extra space.

