## Using Recursion

### Intuition

* Reversing an array means **exchanging opposite elements**.

* Start from the beginning and swap with the matching element from the end.

* After each swap, move one step forward and repeat the same idea.

* Stop when reaching the **middle**, since everything is already reversed.

### Approach

* Use recursion to reverse the array gradually.
* Swap elements from the beginning and end.
* Stop when the middle of the array is reached.
* Continue recursion for the next position.

