# Palindrome of a String

## Recursive Solution

### Intuition

* A palindrome looks identical when read from left to right and right to left.

* To verify this, check whether the first and last characters are the same.

* Then move inward and repeat the same check for the next pair.

* Continue this process until a mismatch is found or the middle is reached.

### Approach

* Use recursion to compare characters from both ends of the string.
* If any pair does not match, return false.
* Stop when the middle is reached, returning true.

