# Palindrome with a Twist

## Solution

### Intuition

* We compare characters from both ends because a palindrome is valid only when every mirrored pair matches.

* If the current pair already matches, we simply move inward recursively.

* At the first mismatch, one swap must involve one of these two mismatched positions. Otherwise, that mismatch can never be fixed.

* So from that first bad pair, we try all valid one-swap choices involving the left or right character, and after each trial we recursively check whether the full string becomes a palindrome.

### Approach

* Use one recursive function to move from the outside toward the center and find the first mismatched pair.

* If no mismatch is found, the string is already a palindrome, so return `true`.

* When a mismatch appears at positions `left` and `right`, try swapping `s[left]` with any character equal to `s[right]`, and also try swapping `s[right]` with any character equal to `s[left]`.

* After each swap, use another recursive palindrome check on the full string. If any trial works, return `true`. If all trials fail, return `false`.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```pseudocode
isPalindromeRecursive(s, left, right) {
    /* If pointers cross, the string is a palindrome */
    if (left >= right) {
        return true
    }

    /* If current mirrored characters do not match, it is not a palindrome */
    if (s[left] != s[right]) {
        return false
    }

    /* Continue checking the inner substring */
    return isPalindromeRecursive(s, left + 1, right - 1)
}

canBecomePalindromeRecursive(s, left, right) {
    /* If entire string is checked, it is already a palindrome */
    if (left >= right) {
        return true
    }

    /* If current pair matches, move inward */
    if (s[left] == s[right]) {
        return canBecomePalindromeRecursive(s, left + 1, right - 1)
    }

    /* First mismatch found, so one swap must involve left or right */
    for (i = left + 1 to right) {
        if (s[i] == s[right]) {
            swap(s[left], s[i])

            /* After using one swap, full string must become palindrome */
            if (isPalindromeRecursive(s, 0, length of s - 1)) {
                swap(s[left], s[i])
                return true
            }

            /* Restore original string before next trial */
            swap(s[left], s[i])
        }
    }

    for (i = left to right - 1) {
        if (s[i] == s[left]) {
            swap(s[i], s[right])

            /* After using one swap, full string must become palindrome */
            if (isPalindromeRecursive(s, 0, length of s - 1)) {
                swap(s[i], s[right])
                return true
            }

            /* Restore original string before next trial */
            swap(s[i], s[right])
        }
    }

    /* No single swap can fix the string */
    return false
}

canBecomePalindrome(s) {
    return canBecomePalindromeRecursive(s, 0, length of s - 1)
}
```

</CodeBlock>

### Code Implementation

<MultiLanguageCodeBlock enableMoveCode={true}>

```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class solution {
public:
    bool isPalindromeRecursive(string& s, int left, int right) {
        if (left >= right) {
            return true;
        }

        if (s[left] != s[right]) {
            return false;
        }

        return isPalindromeRecursive(s, left + 1, right - 1);
    }

    bool canBecomePalindromeRecursive(string& s, int left, int right) {
        if (left >= right) {
            return true;
        }

        if (s[left] == s[right]) {
            return canBecomePalindromeRecursive(s, left + 1, right - 1);
        }

        int n = (int)s.size();

        for (int i = left + 1; i <= right; i++) {
            if (s[i] == s[right]) {
                swap(s[left], s[i]);

                if (isPalindromeRecursive(s, 0, n - 1)) {
                    swap(s[left], s[i]);
                    return true;
                }

                swap(s[left], s[i]);
            }
        }

        for (int i = left; i < right; i++) {
            if (s[i] == s[left]) {
                swap(s[i], s[right]);

                if (isPalindromeRecursive(s, 0, n - 1)) {
                    swap(s[i], s[right]);
                    return true;
                }

                swap(s[i], s[right]);
            }
        }

        return false;
    }

    bool canBecomePalindrome(string s) {
        return canBecomePalindromeRecursive(s, 0, (int)s.size() - 1);
    }
};

