# Count the Number of Digits

## Solution

### Intuition

The number of digits in an integer can be found by repeatedly removing the last digit.

* Each division by 10 effectively drops one digit.

* Counting how many times we can do this until the number becomes 0 gives the total digits.

### Approach

* Start a counter at zero.

* Keep dividing the number by 10 to remove the last digit.

* Increment the counter each time a digit is removed.

* Return the counter as the total number of digits.

### Dry Run

