# Counting Digits That Evenly Divide a Number

## Solution 1

### Intuition

* We are asked to count how many digits of a number divide it evenly.
* Think about checking each digit individually: zero cannot divide anything, so skip it.
* For every other digit, see if it divides the original number without a remainder.
* Each time it does, it contributes to our count.
* By iterating through all digits this way, we naturally accumulate the total number of “evenly dividing” digits.

### Approach

* Take each digit of the number one by one.
* Ignore digits that are zero.
* Check if the number can be divided by the digit without remainder.
* Count all digits that divide the number evenly and return the count.

### Dry Run

<div style="position: relative; width: 100%; padding-bottom: 59.27%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;">
  <iframe 
    src="https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vRQN0fSzipoGaLt9pMMQtdO--CIIp833MrREWn07FbqMgcCQ4Qgzc2yvgUTpnW7GLb3gX3-mpRzo1eG/pubembed?start=false&loop=false&delayms=3000" 
    style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border: 0;" 
    allowfullscreen="true" 
    mozallowfullscreen="true" 
    webkitallowfullscreen="true">
  </iframe>
</div>

### Pseudo Code


<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```Pseudocode
evenlyDivides(N) {
    /* Initialize ans to store the count of digits that divide N */
    ans = 0
    /* Copy N into x to manipulate digits without altering N */
    x = N
    /* Process each digit of x */
    while x != 0 {
        /* Extract the last digit of x */
        rem = x % 10
        /* Remove the last digit from x */
        x = x / 10
        /* Skip if the digit is 0 to avoid division by zero */
        if rem == 0 {
            continue
        }
        /* If N is divisible by rem, increment ans */
        if N % rem == 0 {
            ans = ans + 1
        }
    }
    /* Return the total count of digits that evenly divide N */
    return ans
}
```

</CodeBlock>

### Code Implementation

