## Solution 2

### Intuition

* First, observe that a number can have repeating digits, and each occurrence that divides the number counts separately.
* Instead of checking each digit repeatedly, record how many times each digit (1–9) appears. Ignore 0 since it cannot divide.
* Then, for each digit that appears, check if it divides the number evenly.
* If it does, all its occurrences contribute to the count.
* This way, we efficiently combine counting and divisibility, avoiding repeated checks and reducing work.

### Approach

* Count how many times each digit appears in the number.
* Ignore zeros to avoid division by zero.
* For each digit from 1 to 9, check if it divides the number evenly.
* Add all occurrences of divisible digits and return the total count.

### Dry Run

<div style="position: relative; width: 100%; padding-bottom: 59.27%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;">
  <iframe 
    src="https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vQRHlfJEX0342U67DF5sbaQAG6O0StKIk9zhAq6hHiP1aOlJsD90R3HoeqRv0SGVT8iywgE8I00b8tE/pubembed?start=false&loop=false&delayms=3000" 
    style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border: 0;" 
    allowfullscreen="true" 
    mozallowfullscreen="true" 
    webkitallowfullscreen="true">
  </iframe>
</div>

### Pseudo Code


<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```Pseudocode
evenlyDivides(N) {
    /* Initialize a frequency array to count occurrences of each digit 0-9 */
    freq[0..9] = 0
    /* Copy N into temp to extract digits without modifying N */
    temp = N
    /* Count the frequency of each digit in N */
    while temp > 0 {
        /* Increment the count for the last digit */
        freq[temp % 10] = freq[temp % 10] + 1
        /* Remove the last digit from temp */
        temp = temp / 10
    }
    /* Initialize ans to store the total count of digits that divide N */
    ans = 0
    /* Check digits 1 to 9 for divisibility */
    for d = 1 to 9 {
        /* If digit d is present in N and divides N evenly */
        if freq[d] > 0 and N % d == 0 {
            /* Add the number of occurrences of d to ans */
            ans = ans + freq[d]
        }
    }
    /* Return the total count of digits that evenly divide N */
    return ans
}
```

</CodeBlock>

### Dry Run


### Code Implementation

<MultiLanguageCodeBlock enableMoveCode={true}>
```cpp
