# Sum of all Digits Between Numbers

## Solution

### Intuition

The idea is simple:

* Every number is made up of digits.

* We can extract digits one by one using modulo (`% 10`) and division (`/ 10`).

* For each number in the range `[N1, N2]`, compute its digit sum.

* Keep adding these individual digit sums to a running total.

### Approach

* Use a loop to iterate through the range from `N1` to `N2`.

* For each number in the range, extract its digits and calculate their sum.

* Keep a running total of these sums, and finally return the accumulated value as the result.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```
sumOfDigits(num) {
    /* Calculate the sum of digits of a given number */

    sum = 0  /* Initialize sum to 0 */

    while (num > 0) {
        /* Extract the last digit using modulo */
        sum = sum + (num % 10)

        /* Remove the last digit by dividing num by 10 */
        num = num / 10
    }

    return sum  /* Return the total sum of digits */
}

calculateDigitSum(N1, N2) {
    /* Calculate the total sum of digits for all numbers from N1 to N2 (inclusive) */

    totalSum = 0  /* Initialize total sum to 0 */

    for i = N1 to N2 {
        /* Add the sum of digits of the current number i */
        totalSum = totalSum + sumOfDigits(i)
    }

    return totalSum  /* Return the total sum of digits */
}
```
</CodeBlock>

### Code Implementation

<MultiLanguageCodeBlock enableMoveCode={true}>

```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class solution {
public:
    static int sumOfDigits(int num) {
        int sum = 0;
        while (num > 0) {
            sum += num % 10;
            num /= 10;
        }
        return sum;
    }

    static int calculateDigitSum(int N1, int N2) {
        int totalSum = 0;
        for (int i = N1; i <= N2; i++) {
            totalSum += sumOfDigits(i);
        }
        return totalSum;
    }
};

