# Armstrong Number

## Solution

### Intuition

* An Armstrong number equals the sum of its digits each raised to the power of the total number of digits.

* First, figure out how many digits the number has.

* Then, for each digit, calculate its power and add them up.

* Finally, check if this sum matches the original number; if yes, it’s an Armstrong number, otherwise not.

### Approach

- Calculate the number of digits in the given number.
- For each digit, raise it to the power of the total number of digits and add to a sum.
- If the sum equals the original number, return true; otherwise, return false.

### Dry Run

<div style="position: relative; width: 100%; padding-bottom: 59.27%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;">
  <iframe 
    src="https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vR62v4cDZ9wa8bzasPyHk3wrOn9HTlSisHqxhyyzvxOGbZ8ivFp8uESIPPXmiq2n3aYgpgGy9PHRBLy/pubembed?start=false&loop=false&delayms=3000" 
    style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border: 0;" 
    allowfullscreen="true" 
    mozallowfullscreen="true" 
    webkitallowfullscreen="true">
  </iframe>
</div>

### Pseudo Code


<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```
checkArmstrongNumber(num) {
    /* Store original number for comparison */
    x = num
    /* Count number of digits in num */
    n = log10(num) + 1
    /* Initialize sum to store result */
    sum = 0

    /* Extract digits one by one */
    while (x > 0) {
        /* Get last digit */
        digit = x % 10
        /* Add digit raised to power n */
        sum = sum + pow(digit, n)
        /* Remove last digit */
        x = x / 10
    }

    /* If computed sum equals original number */
    if (num == sum) {
        return true
    }

    /* Otherwise, it is not an Armstrong number */
    return false
}

```

</CodeBlock>

### Code Implementation

<MultiLanguageCodeBlock enableMoveCode={true}>

