### Complexity Analysis

* **Time Complexity: `O(n^2)`**

  * The outer loop fixes the starting position of the subarray.
  * The inner loop extends that subarray to every possible ending position while updating the running sum in constant time.
  * The dominant term is `O(n^2)` because all start and end pairs are still checked.

* **Space Complexity: `O(1)`**

  * Only a few variables are used to track the running sum and the best answer.
  * Only constant extra variables are used, costing `O(1)`.
  * Total space used is `O(1)`.

## Solution 3: Optimal Solution (Kadane's Algorithm)

### Intuition

* A negative running sum cannot help any future subarray, because adding it would only make the next result smaller.
* So while scanning the array, we keep the current subarray only as long as it is useful.
* Whenever the running sum becomes negative, we drop it and start fresh from the next position.
* This works because the best subarray ending at any position is either the current element alone or an extension of the previous useful part.

### Approach

* Start with a running sum and a best answer.
* Move through the array from left to right and add each element to the running sum.
* After every update, compare the running sum with the best answer and store the larger one.
* If the running sum becomes negative, reset it to zero because it cannot help later subarrays.
* Return the best answer after the full scan.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```pseudocode
largestSubarraySum(arr) {
    /* Store the size of the array and initialize tracking values */
    n = arr.size()
    curSum = 0
    maxSum = -∞

    /* Scan the array once from left to right */
    for i = 0 to n - 1 {
        curSum = curSum + arr[i]

        /* Update the best subarray sum seen so far */
        maxSum = max(maxSum, curSum)

        /* Reset the running sum if it becomes negative */
        if curSum < 0 {
            curSum = 0
        }
    }

    /* Return the largest subarray sum found */
    return maxSum
}
```

</CodeBlock>

