# Maximum Subarray After Operations

## Positive Sum Extension on Both Sides

### Intuition
- Every element from the second sequence must be placed either in front of or behind the first sequence, so the final arrangement is the original middle sequence surrounded by freely arranged extra elements.
- The best subarray either stays entirely inside the original middle, extends leftward into the prepended side, or extends rightward into the appended side.
- Whenever the subarray extends into the added region, only positive added values help, because any unwanted negative elements can simply be placed far away from the subarray.
- Because the subarray must contain at least one element, whenever the second sequence has no positive values, the best one can still take from that side is its single largest element.
- The answer is the best among the best inner subarray, the positive extension paired with the best prefix, and the positive extension paired with the best suffix.

### Approach
- Scan the second sequence once to compute both the total of its strictly positive values and the overall maximum element, forming the best non-empty block contribution from that side.
- Scan the original sequence to find the best prefix sum while allowing the empty prefix, so this value never goes below zero.
- Scan the original sequence in reverse to find the best suffix sum in the same way.
- Run the classical running-sum technique on the original sequence to find the best non-empty inner subarray total.
- Return the larger of the inner best and the chosen side block plus the larger of the best prefix and best suffix.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language={customtext} showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle={Normal Code}>

```pseudocode
maximizeSubarrayAfterMoves(n, dataA, m, dataB) {

    /* posSumB accumulates all strictly positive values of dataB */
    /* maxB records the largest single element of dataB for the all-negative case */
    posSumB = 0
    maxB = -infinity
    for i = 0 to m - 1 {
        if dataB[i] > 0 {
            posSumB = posSumB + dataB[i]
        }
        if dataB[i] > maxB {
            maxB = dataB[i]
        }
    }

    /* bestBSide is the best non-empty block we can place adjacent to dataA */
    if posSumB > 0 {
        bestBSide = posSumB
    }
    else {
        bestBSide = maxB
    }

    /* maxPrefA is the best prefix sum of dataA with the empty prefix allowed */
    maxPrefA = 0
    running = 0
    for i = 0 to n - 1 {
        running = running + dataA[i]
        if running > maxPrefA {
            maxPrefA = running
        }
    }

    /* maxSufA is the best suffix sum of dataA with the empty suffix allowed */
    maxSufA = 0
    running = 0
    for i = n - 1 down to 0 {
        running = running + dataA[i]
        if running > maxSufA {
            maxSufA = running
        }
    }

    /* kadaneA is the best non-empty subarray sum inside dataA */
    kadaneA = dataA[0]
    best = dataA[0]
    for i = 1 to n - 1 {

        /* Extend the previous window or restart from the current element */
        best = max(dataA[i], best + dataA[i])

        /* Keep the overall best inner window */
        if best > kadaneA {
            kadaneA = best
        }
    }

    /* Pick the larger of best prefix and best suffix as the extension side */
    ext = max(maxPrefA, maxSufA)

    /* Compare the purely inner option with the extended option */
    return max(kadaneA, bestBSide + ext)
}
```

</CodeBlock>

### Code Implementation

<MultiLanguageCodeBlock enableMoveCode={true}>

```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class solution {
public:
    long long maximizeSubarrayAfterMoves(int n, vector<long long>& dataA, int m, vector<long long>& dataB) {
        long long posSumB = 0;
        long long maxB = LLONG_MIN;
        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
            if (dataB[i] > 0) posSumB += dataB[i];
            if ((long long)dataB[i] > maxB) maxB = dataB[i];
        }
        long long bestBSide = (posSumB > 0) ? posSumB : maxB;

        long long maxPrefA = 0, running = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            running += dataA[i];
            if (running > maxPrefA) maxPrefA = running;
        }
        long long maxSufA = 0;
        running = 0;
        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            running += dataA[i];
            if (running > maxSufA) maxSufA = running;
        }

        long long kadaneA = dataA[0], best = dataA[0];
        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            best = max((long long)dataA[i], best + dataA[i]);
            if (best > kadaneA) kadaneA = best;
        }

        long long ext = max(maxPrefA, maxSufA);
        return max(kadaneA, bestBSide + ext);
    }
};

