# Custom Sorting and Popcount Analysis

## Custom Comparator Sorting and Bit Counting

### Intuition

* The first part of the problem is just a custom sorting rule: smaller first values should come earlier, and when those are equal, larger second values should come earlier.
* This works well with sorting because we can directly describe the order we want and let the sorting method arrange all pairs for us.
* For the popcount part, the simplest idea is to look at the binary form of the number and count how many positions contain a one.

### Approach

* Sort all pairs so that smaller first values come first.
* For pairs with the same first value, place the pair with the larger second value earlier.
* Print the sorted pairs in their new order.
* Count how many ones are present in the binary form of the given number and print that count.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
sortPairs(arr) {
    /* Sort all pairs using the required custom order */
    sort arr using rule {

        /* If the first values are different, smaller first value comes earlier */
        if left[0] != right[0] {
            return left[0] < right[0]
        }

        /* If the first values are equal, larger second value comes earlier */
        return left[1] > right[1]
    }

    /* Return the sorted list of pairs */
    return arr
}

popcount(x) {
    /* Initialize the answer that stores the number of set bits */
    count = 0

    /* Keep checking bits until the number becomes zero */
    while x > 0 {

        /* If the last bit is set, increase the answer */
        if x % 2 == 1 {
            count = count + 1
        }

        /* Remove the last bit by shifting the number to the right */
        x = x / 2
    }

    /* Return the total number of set bits */
    return count
}
```

</CodeBlock>

### Code Implementation

<MultiLanguageCodeBlock enableMoveCode={true}>

```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class solution {
public:
    void sortPairs(vector<pair<int, int>>& arr) {
        sort(arr.begin(), arr.end(), [](const pair<int, int>& a, const pair<int, int>& b) {
            if (a.first != b.first) {
                return a.first < b.first;
            }
            return a.second > b.second;
        });
    }

    int popcount(long long x) {
        int count = 0;
        while (x > 0) {
            count += (x & 1);
            x >>= 1;
        }
        return count;
    }
};

