# Sorting a List of Products by Price

## Solution

### Intuition

* We only need to arrange the products by one field, which is the price.

* So the simplest idea is to keep each product together and sort the full list using the price as the comparison value.

* After sorting, printing the list from left to right gives the required order.

### Approach

* Store each product as a pair of name and price.

* Sort the full list in ascending order of price.

* Traverse the sorted list one by one.

* Print each product in the format name:price.

### Pseudocode

```customtext
sortProducts(products) {
    /* Sort the list by price in ascending order */
    sort products based on the second value in increasing order
}

displayProducts(products) {
    /* Print all products in the sorted order */
    for each product in products {
        print product name + ":" + product price
    }
}
```

