```plaintext
secondLargestElement(arr, n){
    /* Sort the array in non-decreasing order */
    sort array arr

    /* Traverse the array from the second last element to the first element */
    for i from n-2 to 0 {
        /* Check if current element is not equal to the largest element */
        if (a[i] != a[n-1]){
            /* Assign the current element as second largest */
            secondLargest = a[i]
            /* Return the second largest element */
            return secondLargest
        }
    }
    /* If no second largest element is found (e.g., all elements are the same), return 0 */
    return 0
}
```

