### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
secondLargestElement(arr, n) {
    /* Initialize max as the first element of the array */
    max = arr[0]

    /* Traverse the array to find the maximum element */
    for i from 0 to n-1 {
        /* If current element is greater than max, update max */
        if (max < arr[i]) {
            max = arr[i]
        }
    }
    /* Initialize second_largest to -1 (default value indicating no second largest yet) */
    second_largest = -1

    /* Traverse the array again to find the second largest element */
    for i from 0 to n-1 {
        /* If current element is greater than second_largest and not equal to max, update second_largest */
        if (arr[i] > second_largest and arr[i] != max) {
            second_largest = arr[i]
        }
    }
    /* Return the second largest element */
    return second_largest
}
```

</CodeBlock>

