### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
secondLargestElement(arr, n) {
    /* Initialize largest element as the first element */
    max = arr[0]
    /* Initialize second largest as -1 (default if not found) */
    second_largest = -1

    /* Traverse array from index 1 to n-1 */
    for i from 1 to n-1 {
        /* If current element is greater than max:
           old max becomes second_largest, and current becomes new max */
        if (arr[i] > max) {
            second_largest = max
            max = arr[i]
        }
        /* If current element lies strictly between second_largest and max,
           update second_largest */
        if (a[i] > second_largest and a[i] < max) {
            second_largest = a[i]
        }
    }
    /* Return the second largest element */
    return second_largest
}
```

</CodeBlock>

