# Sum of Prime Fibonacci Numbers

## Solution

### Intuition

* We only need the first few Fibonacci numbers, so the simplest idea is to build them one by one up to the given position.
* After generating each term, we can check whether that value is prime and add it to the answer if it is.
* This works because every Fibonacci number up to the required position is visited exactly once, and the cost stays small for this problem size.

### Approach

* Start from the first two Fibonacci numbers and handle them as the base of the sequence.
* Generate each next Fibonacci number using the previous two values.
* For every generated value, check whether it is prime.
* Add every prime Fibonacci number to the running sum and return the final total.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language="text" showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle="normal">

```plaintext
isPrime(num) {
    /* Numbers smaller than 2 are not prime */
    if num < 2 {
        /* Return false because prime numbers start from 2 */
        return false
    }

    /* Try all possible divisors up to the square root */
    for i = 2 to i * i <= num {

        /* If any divisor divides completely, the number is not prime */
        if num % i == 0 {

            /* Return false because a valid divisor was found */
            return false
        }
    }

    /* No divisor was found, so the number is prime */
    return true
}

sumOfPrimeFibonacci(N) {
    /* Handle the smallest case where only the first Fibonacci number is considered */
    if N == 1 {

        /* Return 0 because the first Fibonacci number is 0, which is not prime */
        return 0
    }

    /* Start with the first two Fibonacci numbers */
    first = 0
    second = 1

    /* Keep the answer in sum */
    sum = 0

    /* Check the second Fibonacci number separately because it is part of the range */
    if isPrime(second) {

        /* Add it if it is prime */
        sum = sum + second
    }

    /* Build the remaining Fibonacci numbers from the third term to the Nth term */
    for i = 3 to N {

        /* Generate the next Fibonacci number using the previous two */
        current = first + second

        /* Add the current value if it is prime */
        if isPrime(current) {

            /* Update the final answer */
            sum = sum + current
        }

        /* Shift the previous two values forward for the next step */
        first = second
        second = current
    }

    /* Return the total sum of prime Fibonacci numbers */
    return sum
}
```

</CodeBlock>

### Code Implementation

<MultiLanguageCodeBlock enableMoveCode={true}>

```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class solution {
public:
    bool isPrime(int n) {
        if (n <= 1) {
            return false;
        }
        for (int i = 2; i <= sqrt(n); i++) {
            if (n % i == 0) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }

    int fib(int a, int b, int n, int sum, int i) {
        if (i > n) {
            return sum;
        }
        if (isPrime(b)) {
            sum += b;
        }
        return fib(b, a + b, n, sum, i + 1);
    }

    int sumOfPrimeFibonacci(int n) {
        if (n < 2) {
            return 0;
        }
        return fib(0, 1, n, 0, 1);
    }
};

