### Complexity Analysis

* **Time Complexity: `O(log N)`**

  * The algorithm performs a modified binary search.

  * In each iteration, it discards half of the search space by identifying which half is sorted.

  * Hence, the number of iterations is logarithmic, so the time complexity is `O(log N)`.

* **Space Complexity: `O(1)`**

  * Only a few variables (`low`, `high`, `mid`) are used.

  * No extra space proportional to input size is required, so space complexity is `O(1)`.

# Largest Element

## Brute Force Approach

### Intuition

* Sorting arranges all numbers in increasing order.
* After sorting, the maximum value naturally shifts to the last position.
* So we can return the last element as the largest.

### Approach

- Sort the array and print the last element (`arr[n-1]`).

