## Solution 3 : Bit Manipulation

### Intuition

Instead of searching for the missing value directly, think about how numbers behave when they meet their identical partner. With XOR, equal values cancel each other completely.

Now imagine combining every value from the expected range with every value from the array. All numbers that appear in both places will quietly eliminate themselves. Since exactly one number is absent, it never finds a partner to cancel it.

After all cancellations finish, only that unmatched value remains — which is precisely the missing number.

### Approach

* Use the XOR rule where same numbers cancel each other.
* Combine all numbers from the expected range with the array values.
* All matching numbers disappear automatically.
* The value left at the end is the missing number.

